text.tspan: The Mystery of the Universe, the Meaning of Life
What radiance bright! The Word is God revealed to me,
Ent’ring as light—my path is clear, no more I’ll stray.
God’s Word contains life, truth, reality;
What sweet employ! The church life is my heart’s desire!
Eat, drink, enjoy! In me each day, more life divine.
Christ is supplied, increased; God’s house built; then
God’s glorified—on earth as in the heav’n.
